title: FireFox Version 89 Refuses to do anything
content: Firefox used to be such a great browser. It worked perfectly yesterday. Now it won't load a single page. I'm posting this question from the Chrome browser, which works so much better than Firefox right now. I am using a Windows 10 OS if that info is needed. My question is: Why does the Firefox browser refuse to work now? I type in a URL and it wont even show a loading bar, it just sits there, I can't even access the settings page, nothing is working at all with this browser. I can still see the bookmarks bar but when I click on them, nothing will load. What is wrong with Firefox?

title: Roblox 'An error occurred trying to launch the experience. Please try again later.' Error Message (only FireFox)
content:
Hi

I'm trying to play Roblox on my laptop through Firefox. None of the games I click play on even try to load, they just say the message 'An error occurred trying to launch the experience. Please try again later.'

When I tried in Microsoft Edge (which I never use) the games launched fine.

I tried clearing cookies but that did not fix the issue.

Any ideas?
